<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Bamazon</title>
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="<%= image_url('b.png') %>" />
    <link href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-wvfXpqpZZVQGK6TAh5PVlGOfQNHSoD2xbE+QkPxCAFlNEevoEH3Sl0sibVcOQVnN" crossorigin="anonymous">   
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application' %>
    <% if current_user %>
    <script>
      window.currentUser ={
        'id': <%= current_user.id%>,
        "username": '<%= current_user.username%>',
        'email': '<%= current_user.email %>'
      }
    </script>
    <%end%>
    <meta property="og:title" content = "Project Title" />
    <meta property="og:image" content = "<%= image_url('bamazon_pic.png') %>" />
    <meta property="og:description" content = "A full-stack single-page Amazon clone where users can browse, add to the cart, and purchase the products as well as write reviews for the product. I utilized React to ensure a single page feature. I designed action controllers using AJAX request and Ruby on Rails to send an HTTP request for the actions like destroy, create, and update the reviews and orders. I connected the rails backend to AWS S3 for images of the project to reduce space complexity in Heroku and GitHub." />
    <meta property="og:url" content = "https://bamazon-lyhour.herokuapp.com/#/" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <%= yield %>
    <div class="loader-wrapper">
        <span class="loader"><span class="loader-inner"></span></span>
    </div>

    <script>
        $(window).on("load", function () {
                $(".loader-wrapper").fadeOut("slow");
            });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>